    SignalOffloader
    public class DelegatingSignalOffloader
extends java.lang.Object
implements SignalOffloader

      • offloadSubscribe

        public <T> void offloadSubscribe​(PublisherSource.Subscriber<? super T> subscriber,
                                 java.util.function.Consumer<PublisherSource.Subscriber<? super T>> handleSubscribe)
        Description copied from interface: SignalOffloader
        Offloads subscribe call for the passed PublisherSource.Subscriber.

        Offloading Failures

        Implementations are expected to handle failure to offload, e.g. If a thread pool is used to offload and it rejects task submissions. In such situations, it is expected that the passed PublisherSource.Subscriber will be correctly terminated.

        Caution

        This method MUST not be called concurrently with itself or other offload methods here on the same SignalOffloader instance.
        Specified by:
        offloadSubscribe in interface SignalOffloader
        Type Parameters:
        T - Type of signal.
        Parameters:
        subscriber - PublisherSource.Subscriber for which subscribe call has to be offloaded.
        handleSubscribe - Consumer to handle the offloaded subscribe call.
